#
#  Maintained by Howard Jones (howardjones/network-weathermap) since
#  2005.  430 GH stars.  PHP Network Weathermap is a NETWORK TOPOLOGY
#  DIAGRAM GENERATOR widely used by NOCs (Network Operations Centers)
#  to produce live-data-driven SVG/PNG diagrams of network links and
#  nodes — pulls bandwidth/utilization data from RRD files (Cacti,
#  Munin, MRTG, observium) and renders weighted/colored network maps
#  with traffic flow arrows.  De facto standard for visualizing
#  network telemetry alongside Cacti.  Sister tools: Cacti (PHP
#  network monitoring, IN CORPUS via _cacti), Observium (commercial
#  network monitoring), LibreNMS (in corpus), SmokePing (in corpus),
#  RRDtool (in corpus via _rrdtool).
#
#  CLI library taxonomy update: 3rd PHP CLI library — Ulrich Schmidt-
#  Goertz's **GetOpt PHP** library (ulrichsg/getopt-php).  PHP
#  ecosystem now has 3 documented CLI libraries (R282 PHP stdlib
#  getopt + R356 Symfony Console + R388 GetOpt PHP).
#
#  GetOpt PHP (ulrichsg/getopt-php / `ulrichsg/getopt-php` on
#  Packagist) is Ulrich Schmidt-Goertz's modern object-oriented PHP
#  CLI parser library — provides a Composer-installable alternative
#  to PHP's stdlib `getopt()` function (R282) and Symfony Console
#  (R356).  Distinct from PHP's stdlib `getopt()` (procedural function
#  with mixed-array return value) and Symfony Console (full FRAMEWORK
#  with Command classes + DependencyInjection + Console::run() event
#  dispatcher) by being a FOCUSED PARSE-ONLY LIBRARY with object-
#  oriented API.  Used by PHP Network Weathermap (430 stars, NOC
#  network topology), Howard Jones's NOC tooling, Google Ads PHP SDK
#  examples, Balloon ECM platform (gyselroth/balloon), oforge
#  e-commerce, Ko Worker job runners, OVH CLI by miklinux, AWS
#  Instance Connect, JBZoo PHPUnit, syncdrive (martok), and many
#  PHP CLI tools that need richer parsing than stdlib `getopt()` but
#  don't want the full Symfony Console framework.
#
#  GetOpt PHP API:
